{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/sliders\/overflowsliderguide"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A deep dive into "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSlider","isActive":true},{"text":" — a meter-style slider with two moving parts and velocity-based gestures.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders"]]},"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","roleHeading":"API Collection","modules":[{"name":"Sliders"}],"title":"OverflowSlider Guide"},"topicSections":[{"title":"Essentials","anchor":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSlider","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSliderStyle","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSliderConfiguration","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/TickMarks"]},{"title":"Tutorials","anchor":"Tutorials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/tutorials\/OverflowSlider-Tutorials"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Guides","anchor":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/LSliderGuide","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/DoubleLSliderGuide","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/RSliderGuide","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/DoubleRSliderGuide","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/TrackPadGuide","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/RadialPadGuide","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/JoystickGuide","doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/PSliderGuide"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSliderGuide","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSlider","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a slider with a fixed frame but a movable track in the background. It is designed for values that have a discrete nature but would not necessarily fit on screen. Both the thumb and track can be dragged independently."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"What it does","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"What-it-does"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"thumb","type":"text"}]},{"text":" can be dragged within a fixed frame.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"track"}]},{"type":"text","text":" can be dragged and thrown — velocity is preserved and decays gradually."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When the thumb reaches the minimum or maximum of its bounds, velocity is added to the track in the opposite direction."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Uses tick marks along the track to provide a meter-like visual.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Parameters","type":"heading","text":"Parameters"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Parameter"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Type","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Default"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Description","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding<Double>"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"required"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The value the slider should control"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"range","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"ClosedRange<Double>","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"required"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The minimum and maximum numbers that "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" can be"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"spacing","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"required"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The spacing of the slider’s tick marks","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isDisabled"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Bool"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Whether the slider should be disabled"}]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Basic-Usage","text":"Basic Usage","level":2},{"type":"codeListing","code":["@State private var value = 50.0","","OverflowSlider(value: $value, range: 0...500, spacing: 10, isDisabled: false)","    .frame(height: 60)"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Adjusting Tick Spacing","anchor":"Adjusting-Tick-Spacing","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"spacing","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameter controls how far apart the tick marks are, in value-domain units:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["OverflowSlider(value: $value, range: 0...1000, spacing: 25, isDisabled: false)","    .frame(height: 60)"]},{"anchor":"Velocity-Behaviour","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Velocity Behaviour"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both the thumb and track respond to gestures with velocity. When you throw the track by dragging quickly and releasing, momentum carries it forward and decays gradually. When the thumb hits a boundary, the track begins to scroll in the opposite direction automatically."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"OverflowSliderConfiguration","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"OverflowSliderConfiguration"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Both style methods provide access to state values through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSliderConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct OverflowSliderConfiguration {","    let isDisabled: Bool","    let thumbIsActive: Bool","    let thumbIsAtLimit: Bool","    let trackIsActive: Bool","    let trackIsAtLimit: Bool","    let value: Double","    let min: Double","    let max: Double","    let tickSpacing: Double","}"]},{"anchor":"Styling","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Styling"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Conform to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/OverflowSliderStyle","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and implement two methods:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeThumb(configuration:)"},{"text":" — the draggable thumb in the foreground","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"makeTrack(configuration:)"},{"type":"text","text":" — the movable background track with tick marks"}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apply with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".overflowSliderStyle(_:)"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["struct MyOverflowSliderStyle: OverflowSliderStyle {","    func makeThumb(configuration: OverflowSliderConfiguration) -> some View {","        RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 5)","            .fill(configuration.thumbIsActive ? Color.orange : Color.blue)","            .opacity(0.5)","            .frame(width: 20, height: 50)","    }","","    func makeTrack(configuration: OverflowSliderConfiguration) -> some View {","        let totalLength = configuration.max - configuration.min","        let spacing = configuration.tickSpacing","","        return TickMarks(","            spacing: CGFloat(spacing),","            ticks: Int(totalLength \/ Double(spacing))","        )","        .stroke(Color.gray)","        .frame(width: CGFloat(totalLength))","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Apply the style:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["OverflowSlider(value: $value, range: 0...500, spacing: 10, isDisabled: false)","    .overflowSliderStyle(MyOverflowSliderStyle())","    .frame(height: 60)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"overflowSliderStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier cascades through the view hierarchy."}]}]}],"references":{"doc://Sliders/documentation/Sliders/DoubleLSlider":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DoubleLSlider","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A spatially adaptive linear range slider with a lower thumb, an upper thumb,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and a draggable active-track segment between them.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DoubleLSlider"}],"title":"DoubleLSlider","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/DoubleLSlider","url":"\/documentation\/sliders\/doublelslider"},"doc://Sliders/documentation/Sliders/JoystickGuide":{"title":"Joystick Guide","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Sliders\/documentation\/Sliders\/JoystickGuide","url":"\/documentation\/sliders\/joystickguide","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[{"text":"A deep dive into ","type":"text"